OL,3,CJersey Lifeboat Association suspension
OL,4,C'unjust and oppressive'
OL,6,FThe Board found the review which
OL,7,Fresulted in the suspension was
OL,8,Fcommissioned without lawful authority
OL,9,Fby the Harbourmaster and despite that,
OL,10,Fnothing in the report would warrant
OL,11,Fhim recommending such a decision.
OL,13,FThe investigation should have been
OL,14,Fauthorised by the elected minister
OL,15,Fwith responsibility for the Ports of
OL,16,FJersey, then Deputy Lyndon Farnham,
OL,17,Fwho confirmed he did not permit it to
OL,18,Fgo ahead.
